05473nam a22009255i 9783110675481DE-B159720230228015514.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106754817 a10.1515/97831106754812doi  a(DE-B1597)536003  a(OCoLC)1138527124  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aREL0370302bisacsh1 aAždajić, Dejan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Shaping Shaikh :bThe Role of the Shaikh in Lived Islam among Sufis in Bosnia and Herzegovina /cDejan Aždajić. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (XII, 282 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aReligion and Society ,x1437-5370 ;v8500tFrontmatter -- tAcknowledgements -- tContents -- tTable of Figures -- tChapter 1: Introduction -- tChapter 2: Exploring the Field -- tChapter 3: The Centrality of the Shaikh -- tChapter 4: The Theological Dimension of Guidance -- tChapter 5: The Practical Dimension of Guidance -- tChapter 6: Conclusion -- tGlossary: A Note on Transliteration and Pronunciation -- tBibliography: Primary Sources -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIslam is more than a system of rigid doctrines and normative principles. It is a diverse mosaic of subjective, often contradictory interpretations and discrepant applications that prohibit a narrow, one-dimensional approach. This book argues that to uncover this complex reality and achieve a more accurate understanding of Islam as a lived religion, it is imperative to consider Islam from the point of view of human beings who practice their faith. Consequently, this book provides an important contribution through a detailed ethnographic study of two contemporary Sufi communities. Although both groups shared much in common, there was a fundamental, almost perplexing range of theological convictions and ritual implementations. This book explores the mechanism that accounts for such diversity, arguing for a direct correlation between Sufi multiformity and the agency of the spiritual leader, the Shaikh. Empirical research regarding the authority by which Shaikhs subjectively generate legitimate adaptations that shape the contours of religious belief are lacking. This study is significant, because it focuses on how leadership operates in Sufism, highlighting the primacy of the Shaikh in the selection and appropriation of inherited norms.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aNaqshabandīyahzBosnia and Herzegovina. 0aShaykh al-IslāmzBosnia and Herzegovina. 4aEthnografie. 4aIslam. 4aScheich. 4aSufismus. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Rituals & Practice.2bisacsh  aEthnography.  aIslam.  aShaikh.  aSufism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831106755590 cprintz978311067546740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311067548140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110675481423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110675481/original  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2